{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium is a generic library for creating and working with "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"concrete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"syntax trees"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" (CSTs)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Traditional” abstract syntax trees (ASTs) usually contain different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types of nodes which represent different syntactical elements of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"source text of a document and reduce its information to the minimal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"amount necessary to correctly interpret it. In contrast, CSTs are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"lossless"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" representations of the entire input where all tree nodes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are represented homogeneously (the nodes are "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"untyped"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":") but tagged"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/RawSyntaxKind"},{"type":"text","text":" to determine the kind of grammatical element"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"they represent."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One big advantage of this representation is that it can recreate the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"original source exactly while also lending itself very well to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"representation of "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"incomplete or erroneous"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" trees and is thus highly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"suited for usage in contexts such as IDEs or any other application"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where a user is "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"editing"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" the source text."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The concept and the data structures for Cambium’s syntax trees are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"inspired in part by Swift’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift\/tree\/5e2c815edfd758f9b1309ce07bfc01c4bc20ec23\/lib\/Syntax","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and by the Rust "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"library, which itself is a fork of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/rust-analyzer\/rowan\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" developed by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"authors of "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/rust-analyzer\/rust-analyzer\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Two-layer storage","anchor":"Two-layer-storage","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Trees consist of two layers:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The inner "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"green tree","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" contains the actual source text as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"position-independent green nodes. Tokens and nodes that appear"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identically at multiple places in the source are deduplicated in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this representation in order to store the tree efficiently. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"means that a green tree may structurally be a DAG rather than a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unique object per source position."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To remedy this, the real syntax tree is constructed on top of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"green tree as a secondary tree (called the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"red tree","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":") which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"models the exact source structure."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As a possible third layer, a strongly typed AST can be built on top of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the red tree (see "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/GettingStarted#AST-Layer"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Notable differences from `cstree`","anchor":"Notable-differences-from-cstree","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium tracks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cstree"},{"type":"text","text":"’s practical guarantees but uses modern Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"language features rather than imitating Rust mechanically:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Borrowed cursors are the primary traversal API.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Walking a tree"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uses "},{"code":"~Copyable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s borrowed inside a closure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"scope. There are no per-node retains during traversal, no implicit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"array allocation for child iteration, and no surprise copies of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"red node references. Copyable "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s exist for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"long-lived references but are an explicit opt-in."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Move-only builders, caches, and trees.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumBuilder\/GreenNodeCache","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"~Copyable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Ownership boundaries are visible in the type system;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you cannot accidentally clone a builder or duplicate a parse cache."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Synchronous traversal, ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" snapshots.","type":"text"}]},{"text":" Tree navigation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"never goes through an actor. Once a tree is built it can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"promoted to a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree"},{"text":" with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree\/intoShared()"},{"text":" and freely shared across actors and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tasks.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Witness-based change tracking.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Editing a tree returns a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" describing the structural change; an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"incremental reparse returns a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" listing the subtrees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that were carried over by reference. Cambium does not bake an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identity-tracker into the core; consumers translate identities","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through witness chains.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"No mutation in place.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Trees are persistent. Editing produces a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"new tree that shares as much green storage with the old as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"possible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Strict serialization.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Snapshots written by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree\/serializeGreenSnapshot()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and read by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumSerialization\/GreenSnapshotDecoder","type":"reference"},{"text":" are length-, hash-, and kind-validated at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"every record. Bad snapshots are rejected with named errors.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Modules","anchor":"Modules","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium is split into several focused modules. Importing the umbrella"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Cambium"},{"type":"text","text":" module re-exports the runtime modules; test support and macros"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are imported explicitly when you need them. You can also pick individual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modules directly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumCore","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — The foundational layer: ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/RawSyntaxKind","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/TextSize","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/GreenNode","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/GreenToken","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumBuilder","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder","type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumBuilder\/GreenNodeCache","type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumBuilder\/LocalTokenInterner","type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumBuilder\/SharedTokenInterner","type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"SharedSyntaxTree.replacing(_:with:cache:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumIncremental","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental\/ParseInput","type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental\/IncrementalParseSession","type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental\/ReuseOracle","type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumAnalysis","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumAnalysis\/Diagnostic","type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumAnalysis\/SyntaxMetadataStore","type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","ty